<h3>Greptile Summary</h3>

This PR fixes a macOS default browser detection failure where LaunchServices stores a different bundle ID (e.g., `com.microsoft.edgemac`) than what `osascript`'s `path to application id` lookup expects (e.g., `com.microsoft.Edge`), causing the browser to not be detected even though it is installed and set as default.

The fix introduces a `KNOWN_BUNDLE_ID_PATHS` map that covers LaunchServices-style bundle IDs for common Chromium-based browsers and updates `detectDefaultChromiumExecutableMac()` to fall back to these hardcoded paths whenever the `osascript`/`defaults` resolution chain fails. The fallback correctly validates file existence before accepting the path, and the two-stage approach (try dynamic resolution first, then fall back) is the right design.

**Key changes:**
- Adds `KNOWN_BUNDLE_ID_PATHS` mapping LaunchServices bundle IDs (e.g., `com.microsoft.edgemac*`, `com.brave.Browser`, `com.google.Chrome`, etc.) to their conventional `/Applications/...` executable paths.
